    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 24, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🔐 OpenAI's New \"Cyber\" Model Is Already Briefing the Pentagon\n\nOpenAI briefed ~50 cyber defense practitioners in Washington on April 22, introducing GPT-5.4-Cyber — a model purpose-built for binary reverse engineering and vulnerability analysis.\n\n- **The access structure:** A tiered-access program for US federal agencies and Five Eyes allies. The model isn't yet available to government users (discussions ongoing), but the briefings have started.\n- **The capability:** Read compiled code, figure out what it does, find exploitable holes. This is what nation-state hackers do — automated.\n\n*OpenAI's pivot to government cybersecurity is happening faster than their pivot to profit.*\n\n**Sources:** [Axios](https://www.axios.com/2026/04/22/openai-gpt-cyber-government-meeting) | [OpenAI Blog](https://openai.com/index/scaling-trusted-access-for-cyber-defense/) | [The Hacker News](https://thehackernews.com/2026/04/openai-launches-gpt-54-cyber-with.html)\n\n---\n\n## 💰 DeepSeek Is Taking Money — From the Two Companies That Fear It Most\n\nDeepSeek is in talks for its first-ever funding round, targeting a $20 billion+ valuation. Tencent and Alibaba are both in discussions. Tencent reportedly wants up to 20%; DeepSeek is resisting that level of control.\n\n- **The irony:** DeepSeek spooked China's tech giants in January 2025 by matching frontier AI at a fraction of the cost. Now those same giants want to buy a piece of it — before it eats more of their market.\n- **The context:** DeepSeek V4, a 1-trillion-parameter Mixture-of-Experts model, has already missed multiple late-April launch targets. Taking its first money from direct competitors is a very particular kind of leverage.\n\n*DeepSeek built a model that terrified the industry. The industry's response: invest in it.*\n\n**Sources:** [Bloomberg](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2026-04-22/deepseek-in-talks-to-raise-at-20-billion-value-the-information) | [The Information](https://www.theinformation.com/articles/tencent-alibaba-talks-invest-deepseek-20-billion-plus-valuation)\n\n---\n\n## 🪦 Meta Is Cutting 8,000 Jobs. The Budget Line Is \"AI.\"\n\nMeta announced April 23 it will eliminate 10% of its workforce — approximately 8,000 employees — beginning May 20, while simultaneously scrapping 6,000 planned hires.\n\n- **The math:** 8,000 cuts + 6,000 positions scrapped = 14,000 fewer humans at Meta by year-end. The official framing: \"ramping up AI investments.\"\n- **The pattern:** Atlassian cut 5% citing AI. Duolingo replaced contractors with AI in February. Meta joins a growing list of companies where \"AI investment\" and \"headcount\" are now competing for the same budget line.\n\n*Meta is investing heavily in AI. The investment is most visible in the HR department.*\n\n**Sources:** [CNBC](https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/23/meta-will-cut-10percent-of-workforce-as-it-pushes-more-into-ai.html)"
  }
]
